title.narrative: COMMUNICATIONS, ADVOCACY AND PARTNERSHIP ON CHILDREN S RIGHTS

description.narrative: UNICEF staff and partners are provided tools, guidance and resources to improve communications and advocate for and establish partnerships on children's rights issues., which contributes to Communication And Advocacy, Cross-Sectoral - Human Rights, Cross-Sectoral - Other Programme Areas, Cross-Sectoral - Other Programme Areas (Covid), Private Sector Engagement. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Communications, Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: The country programme is effectively coordinated, managed and supported to achieve results for children

description.narrative: In 2021, UNICEF advanced its external communication and advocacy on key issues related to the situation of children and their families in Ukraine by growing its digital networks, creating engaging content, strengthening youth engagement, fostering its media outreach, building new partnerships with business and extending its alliances with key stakeholders for the promotion of important child rights’ issues, such as immunization, access to education, inclusion, deinstitutionalization, child poverty, mental health, climate changes and children wellbeing during the pandemic.; | Status:On-track | As-of Date:25/01/2022
